1.00	Spanish_is_the_Loving_Tongue	Spanish is the Loving Tongue	"Spanish is the Loving Tongue" is a song based on the poem "A Border Affair" written by Charles Badger Clark in 1907. Clark was a cowboy poet who lived throughout the American West, and was named the Poet Laureate of South Dakota in 1930. The poem was set to music in 1925 by Billy Simon. Over the years, the song was recorded by many top recording artists, including Ian and Sylvia, Bob Dylan, Marianne Faithful, Emmylou Harris, Michael Martin Murphey and Asher Quinn www.asherquinn.co.uk.	
